   "source": [
    "# Referencia Completa de Sintaxis de Rust\n",
    "\n",
    "Este notebook sirve como una guía detallada de la sintaxis y características del lenguaje de programación Rust. Cubre desde los conceptos básicos hasta temas avanzados como el manejo de memoria y concurrencia.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Nota:** Rust evoluciona rápidamente. La mayoría de la sintaxis aquí es estable desde Rust 1.0 (2015), pero se indicará si alguna característica requiere una edición específica (ej. Rust 2018, 2021)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "03e3d012",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Variables y Mutabilidad\n",
    "\n",
    "En Rust, las variables son inmutables por defecto."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "862759e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "El valor de x es: 5\n",
      "z interno: 12\n",
      "z externo: 6\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "// Definición básica (Inmutable)\n",
    "let x = 5;\n",
    "println!(\"El valor de x es: {}\", x);\n",
    "\n",
    "// Variable Mutable\n",
    "let mut y = 5;\n",
    "y = 6;\n",
    "\n",
    "// Constantes\n",
    "const MAX_POINTS: u32 = 100_000;\n",
    "\n",
    "// Shadowing (Sombreado)\n",
    "let z = 5;\n",
    "let z = z + 1; \n",
    "{\n",
    "    let z = z * 2;\n",
    "    println!(\"z interno: {}\", z);\n",
    "}\n",
    "println!(\"z externo: {}\", z);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d843364e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Tipos de Datos\n",
    "\n",
    "### Escalares\n",
    "- **Enteros**: `i8`, `u8`, `i16`, `u16`, `i32` (default), `u32`, `i64`, `u64`, `i128`, `u128`, `isize`, `usize`.\n",
    "- **Flotantes**: `f32`, `f64` (default).\n",
    "- **Booleanos**: `bool` (`true`, `false`).\n",
    "- **Caracteres**: `char` (4 bytes, Unicode)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "bae346f2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "let tup: (i32, f64, u8) = (500, 6.4, 1);\n",
    "let (x, y, z) = tup; // Destructuración\n",
    "let el_primero = tup.0; // Acceso directo\n",
    "\n",
    "let a = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]; // Array (longitud fija)\n",
    "let a_relleno = [3; 5]; // [3, 3, 3, 3, 3]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e5ca876d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Funciones\n",
    "\n",
    "Rust usa *snake case*. La última expresión es el retorno implícito."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e5af6919",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fn suma(a: i32, b: i32) -> i32 {\n",
    "    a + b // Sin punto y coma para retornar\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "fn main() {\n",
    "    let resultado = suma(5, 10);\n",
    "    println!(\"Suma: {}\", resultado);\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e7ed108d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Ownership (Propiedad) y Borrowing\n",
    "\n",
    "Reglas de Oro:\n",
    "1. Cada valor tiene un dueño.\n",
    "2. Solo un dueño a la vez.\n",
    "3. Si el dueño sale de ámbito, el valor se borra."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c8e11e45",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "let s1 = String::from(\"hola\");\n",
    "let s2 = s1; // MOVE: s1 ya no es válida\n",
    "\n",
    "let s3 = s2.clone(); // CLONE: copia profunda\n",
    "\n",
    "// Referencias (Borrowing)\n",
    "let len = calcular_longitud(&s3); // Referencia inmutable\n",
    "\n",
    "fn calcular_longitud(s: &String) -> usize {\n",
    "    s.len()\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// Referencia Mutable\n",
    "let mut s_mut = String::from(\"hola\");\n",
    "modificar(&mut s_mut);\n",
    "\n",
    "fn modificar(s: &mut String) {\n",
    "    s.push_str(\" mundo\");\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4deb7943",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Structs y Enums\n",
    "\n",
    "Rust agrupa datos en Structs y variantes en Enums."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2db5d66c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "struct Rectangulo {\n",
    "    ancho: u32,\n",
    "    alto: u32,\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "impl Rectangulo {\n",
    "    fn area(&self) -> u32 {\n",
    "        self.ancho * self.alto\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "enum Mensaje {\n",
    "    Salir,\n",
    "    Mover { x: i32, y: i32 },\n",
    "    Escribir(String),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "let m = Mensaje::Escribir(String::from(\"Hola\"));"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "91a64550",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Pattern Matching y Control de Flujo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d4a26dbb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Valor: 5\n",
      "Atajo: 5\n",
      "Contando: 1\n",
      "Contando: 2\n",
      "Contando: 3\n",
      "Contando: 4\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "()"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "let algun_valor = Some(5);\n",
    "\n",
    "match algun_valor {\n",
    "    Some(i) => println!(\"Valor: {}\", i),\n",
    "    None => (),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// if let para un solo caso\n",
    "if let Some(i) = algun_valor {\n",
    "    println!(\"Atajo: {}\", i);\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// Loops\n",
    "for i in 1..5 {\n",
    "    println!(\"Contando: {}\", i);\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2bd99d19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Manejo de Errores\n",
    "\n",
    "- `Result<T, E>` para errores recuperables.\n",
    "- `Option<T>` para valores opcionales.\n",
    "- `panic!` para errores no recuperables."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "477238d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use std::fs::File;\n",
    "\n",
    "fn abrir_archivo() -> Result<File, std::io::Error> {\n",
    "    let f = File::open(\"test.txt\")?;\n",
    "    Ok(f)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "// unwrap() o expect() si estás seguro o quieres crash\n",
    "// let f = File::open(\"test.txt\").expect(\"No se pudo abrir\");"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "05820e6c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Colecciones\n",
    "\n",
    "- `Vec<T>`: Vectores dinámicos.\n",
    "- `String`: Strings UTF-8 en el heap.\n",
    "- `HashMap<K, V>`: Diccionarios."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b053dd8d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "let mut v = vec![1, 2, 3];\n",
    "v.push(4);\n",
    "\n",
    "use std::collections::HashMap;\n",
    "let mut mapa = HashMap::new();\n",
    "mapa.insert(String::from(\"Azul\"), 10);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "500f0b33",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Traits y Genéricos\n",
    "\n",
    "Similar a interfaces."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c5854016",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pub trait Resumible {\n",
    "    fn resumir(&self) -> String;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "struct Noticia { titular: String }\n",
    "\n",
    "impl Resumible for Noticia {\n",
    "    fn resumir(&self) -> String {\n",
    "        format!(\"Noticia: {}\", self.titular)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a6b340f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Concurrencia"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1da164b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "use std::thread;\n",
    "use std::sync::{Arc, Mutex};\n",
    "\n",
    "let contador = Arc::new(Mutex::new(0));\n",
    "let mut handles = vec![];\n",
    "\n",
    "for _ in 0..10 {\n",
    "    let contador = Arc::clone(&contador);\n",
    "    let handle = thread::spawn(move || {\n",
    "        let mut num = contador.lock().unwrap();\n",
    "        *num += 1;\n",
    "    });\n",
    "    handles.push(handle);\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "for handle in handles { handle.join().unwrap(); }\n",
    "println!(\"Resultado: {}\", *contador.lock().unwrap());"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5681cd75",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11. Referencia de Versiones y Características Modernas\n",
    "\n",
    "### Rust 1.39+\n",
    "- `async` / `.await`: Programación asíncrona.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Rust 1.51+\n",
    "- **Const Generics**: `struct Array<T, const N: usize> { data: [T; N] }`.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Rust 1.65+\n",
    "- **let-else**: `let Some(x) = opcional else { return };` para salida temprana limpia.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Rust 1.70+\n",
    "- **OnceLock<T>** y **OnceCell<T>**: Inicialización única segura en la librería estándar (reemplaza `lazy_static` en muchos casos).\n",
    "\n",
    "### Macros\n",
    "- `macro_rules!`: Macros declarativas.\n",
    "- `#[derive(...)]`: Macros procedimentales para implementar comportamiento automático."
   ]
  }
